OL,6,FJudge Denis Watson said: "The cost of
OL,7,Frepair of the shelter is significant,
OL,8,Fbut it seems to me that the amount of
OL,9,Fcompensation I could order is such a
OL,10,Ftoken that the public may wonder what
OL,11,Fon earth the judge is doing. I will
OL,12,Fleave it to the local authority if
OL,13,Fthey wish to pursue such a claim for
OL,14,Fthe restoration."
OL,16,FHe added: "Mr Mason, you may not be
OL,17,Fout of the woods yet. You may well
OL,18,Ffind Sefton Council will pursue you
OL,19,Ffor the cost of the repair of the
OL,20,Fshelter."
